=============================================
How to run and test ResilientHMM
=============================================

0. Build Libray

> make all

m3rlite.example.jar and m3rlite.jar will be generated in lib/

1. Running

You can run a example of ResilientHMM.
> X10_RESILIENT_MODE=1 X10_NPLACES=2 x10 -logconf logging.properties -cp lib/m3rlite.jar:lib/m3rlite.example.jar com.ibm.m3rlite.example.ResilientHMM 2 6 100 10 0.001 testdata/sample.dat

Options 
./ResilientHMM <number of hidden states> <number of observation types> <number of input lines> <maximum iterations> <eps> <learning data>


2. Learning data file format
You can preapre your own learning data. Each line is separated with space, and it contains observation symbols, like that "1 2 3 4 5". 
